[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=d6be7a4ae93&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=d6be7a4ae93&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17936&quot; title=&quot;New admin ui navigation sidebar is missing focus indicators&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17936&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17936&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: add focus indicator to navigation sidebar entries (#3744)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rather than using Tab, which does not have colors for our various states,&lt;br/&gt;
we use Button, which has all colors except for the Selected state.&lt;br/&gt;
Material 3&apos;s new &quot;Expressive&quot; version also provides an experiment ToggleButton&lt;br/&gt;
component, but our version of the Material 3 dependency is not new enough to&lt;br/&gt;
be able to use it (and if I understand correctly, we can&apos;t use the very newest&lt;br/&gt;
material 3 release, since Compose Multiplatform does not yet support it).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With thanks to @malliaridis for the guidance getting started, and for&lt;br/&gt;
suggesting that we try a component other than Tab.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
